<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
<title>CSS Test: page properties: background properties</title>
<link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#page-properties"/>
<meta name="flags" content="paged" />
<meta name="assert" content="Background properties defined in CSS2.1 apply to the page box."/>
<style type="text/css">
	@page { 
		margin: 7%;
		background: #98fb98;
	}
	html, body {margin: 0;}
</style>
</head>
<body>
	<p>When printed, this page must have a green background that covers the entire page. If any white shows around the edges, it must be a very narrow strip.</p>
</body>
</html>